<br>
The fansites were all featuring interviews and spoilers in which things such as the Bazaar function were discused(not implemented so far, but HEY, the premium server already has an automap, and it's not even LIVE yet!).  The point most folks seem to be choking on is that Luclin CONTENT isn't even all live, let alone interface upgrades, but resources have been apparently devoted to this Legends program.<br>
<br>
For instance, one of the high level raid zones in the new expansion isn't live.  The places are all there, and there's a quest to get the key to the zone, and the big boss MoB is already rendered and pacing in his little sanctum, but the key quest is broken.  It's intentional.  Triton, a guild on Povar already HAS keys to this place.  They've received confirmation from server GM's that this was indeed the key, but it doesn't work.<br>
<br>
Here's a little insult for you to sprinkle on the injury:  a few guilds have gotten in with various tricks and killed the guy, and they took the time to code in loot for him....JOKE LOOT!  He drops a breastplate that's -200ish to most stats called the Curiass of Sad Exploitation, and a tremendous sword that nobody can equip.  Not only have they not finished the content, they've taken the time to put in surrogate content to deride the folks who can bypass the broken bits and get to it!<br>
<br>
Now we see that while they couldn't implement a great deal of what they were promising with SoL, they DID have time to code new interfaces, and add features to the game that we paid for, but will never see.  We see that the content and service that we were promised when EQ went live, and arguably have yet to see, is available for an extra thirty bones a month?!  I don't know who coined it, but the sentiment seems to be:<br>
<br>
&quot;You're in our world now, and the rent just went up.&quot;<br>
<br>
